You can view the query behind your lens in CRM Analytics by clicking Query Mode. You can edit the underlying code written as you explore, or copy it for use elsewhere.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

To view visualizations:
Use CRM Analytics
Explore a dataset to get the visualization or table of data you want
Click Query Mode to view the query's SAQL or SOQL code

For more information about SAQL, see the CRM Analytics SAQL Developer Guide.

Tips and Considerations when Working with Lens Queries:

* To work with multiple datasets simultaneously, reference them in the JSON editor for the currently running lens.
* If you run a query while exploring, the filters become read-only while in chart and table modes.
* If you save the lens with filters in read-only mode, they remain in read-only mode.
title: Viewing Queries Behind Lenses in CRM Analytics
